{"data": [{"id": "4743219", "title": "Mullen Group: An Improving Outlook After A Strong Q3", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Truck driving on remote highway\" data-id=\"594827553\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Jetta Productions Inc</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>Please note all $ figures are in $CAD, not $USD, unless otherwise stated. </em></p> <h2><strong>Introduction </strong></h2> <p>The transportation and logistics sector may be showing signs of life again, which has brought me back to one of my favourite Canadian</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/594827553/image_594827553.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743219-mullen-group-stock-improving-outlook-after-a-strong-q3", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:45:29"}, {"id": "4743216", "title": "Micron Is On A Mission To Penetrate The HBM Market - Buy It", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"People walking in a maze shaped as a brain\" data-id=\"1194975140\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1152px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Hiroshi Watanabe/DigitalVision via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Investment Thesis</h2> <p>The semiconductor memory market is witnessing a few history-altering moments that are sure to change the course of the entire industry. GenAI already did its bit to rock the boat enough to create a</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1194975140/image_1194975140.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743216-micron-stock-on-a-mission-to-penetrate-the-hbm-market-buy-it", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:38:09"}, {"id": "4743214", "title": "Micron Q1 Preview: Mixed Signals Going Into Earnings", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Taking decisions for the future\" data-id=\"638787162\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">BrianAJackson</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2><span>Performance Assessment</span></h2> <p>My <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4723935-micron-q4-results-didnt-get-me-excited\">last note</a> on Micron (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MU\" title=\"Micron Technology, Inc.\">MU</a></span>) expressed a rather contrarian view as I took a neutral stance amid the bullish cries of analysts from Seeking Alpha, Wall St and even the Quant Ratings. I think my</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/638787162/image_638787162.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743214-micron-q1-preview-mixed-signals-going-into-earnings", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:33:11"}, {"id": "4743226", "title": "Planet Labs PBC 2025 Q3 - Results - Earnings Call Presentation", "description": "<p>The following slide deck was published by Planet Labs PBC in conjunction with their 2025 Q3 earnings call.</p> <p><figure class=\"sa-presentation paywall-full-content invisible\" data-id=\"106087\"></figure></p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743226-planet-labs-pbc-2025-q3-results-earnings-call-presentation", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:23:33"}, {"id": "4743210", "title": "LIT: Buying Lithium At A Bargain", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Lithium mine of silver peak\" data-id=\"1392927109\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"864px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">simonkr/E+ via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>I am bullish on the <strong>LIT Global X Lithium &amp; Battery Tech ETF</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LIT\" title=\"Global X Lithium &amp; Battery Tech ETF\">LIT</a></span>) and I have initiated a long position. Although I believe that the broader market may be headed towards an overheated</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392927109/image_1392927109.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743210-lit-buying-lithium-at-a-bargain", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:20:56"}, {"id": "4743207", "title": "NIO Is Getting Ready For A Fantastic 2025", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt='NIO logo and the Nio\"s user center, NIO House' data-id=\"1271270928\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"4032px\" height=\"3024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Andy Feng</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Deliveries of EV company <strong>NIO Inc. (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NIO\" title=\"NIO Inc.\">NIO</a></span>) </strong>are skyrocketing amid a boost in demand for the company\u2019s new slate of affordable electric vehicles.</p> <p>NIO has started to ship its new Onvo electric vehicles recently, which are met by</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1271270928/image_1271270928.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743207-nio-is-getting-ready-for-a-fantastic-2025", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 12:03:08"}, {"id": "4743205", "title": "Nordic American Tankers: Limited Downside Protection To Weaknesses In The Suezmax Market", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/185275855/image_185275855.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Aerial View of Crude Oil Tanker and Storage Tanks\" data-id=\"185275855\" data-type=\"getty-image\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">Crude Oil Tanker &amp; Storage Tanks</p> <p class=\"item-credits\">rgaydos</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Description</h2> <p><a href=\"https://www.nat.bm/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nordic American Tankers</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NAT\" title=\"Nordic American Tankers Limited\">NAT</a></span>) owns and operates a fleet of 20 <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suezmax\" rel=\"nofollow\">Suezmax</a> tankers, each capable of lifting 1.0 million barrels of oil, or the equivalent of ~160,000 </p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743205-nordic-american-tankers-limited-downside-protection-to-weaknesses-in-the-suezmax-market", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 11:51:07"}, {"id": "4743203", "title": "YETI Holdings: Fairly Valued And Positioned For Success", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Large store billboard of Yeti retail in downtown, wide collection of outdoor products ice chests, vacuum-insulated stainless-steel drinkware, camping, hiking, fishing\" data-id=\"1763925921\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1152px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">TrongNguyen/iStock Editorial via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Investment Thesis</h2> <p>YETI Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YETI\" title=\"YETI Holdings, Inc.\">YETI</a></span>) is establishing a durable competitive advantage across online and brick-and-mortar retail channels. Its flagship drinkware products have been a key driver of success in international markets, positioning the company to expand</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1763925921/image_1763925921.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743203-yeti-holdings-fairly-valued-and-positioned-for-success", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 11:43:01"}, {"id": "4743202", "title": "SoundHound AI: Redefining Business With AI Customer Service Becoming A Critical Utility", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Smiling boy using system AI Chatbot on mobile application. Chatbot conversation, Ai Artificial Intelligence technology. Futuristic technology. Virtual assistant on internet.\" data-id=\"2031369263\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">portishead1/E+ via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>SoundHound AI (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SOUN\" title=\"SoundHound AI, Inc.\">SOUN</a></span>) is a $5.6 billion developer of conversational AI applications, and is leading the way in a generational shift towards a voice-based AI customer service. Along with strides in enterprise solutions, SoundHound has been rapidly expanding</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2031369263/image_2031369263.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743202-soundhound-ai-redefining-business-with-ai-customer-service-becoming-a-critical-utility", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 11:40:35"}, {"id": "4743201", "title": "The Million-Dollar Question Of The American Economy", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Metal globe resting on paper currency\" data-id=\"96502248\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"4843px\" height=\"3632px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Martin Barraud</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p>A large portion of companies in the stock market directly care about the health of the American consumer, yet it is exceedingly difficult to get a read on the consumer because so much of the data seems to conflict. Consumers are simultaneously the richest they have ever been on some metrics, while barely escaping poverty on other metrics.</p> <p>Thus, the million-dollar question for all these consumer-facing companies is: What is the actual state of the American consumer?</p> <p>I'm not entirely able to answer the question, but this article will cover the topic from a variety of angles to provide as much insight as we can. We shall begin with data suggesting the consumer is strong:</p> <h2><strong>Strong Consumer</strong></h2> <p>Real GDP per capita is the highest it has ever been.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-1733780613496261_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1678\" data-height=\"597\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-1733780613496261.png\" alt=\"A graph showing a line Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>This is a real figure, meaning it is already inflation adjusted.</p> <p>GDP is interesting from a national level, but not as relevant to individual consumers. The average consumer's health is going to be more closely tied to median household income.</p> <p>There are 2 primary differences between median household income and GDP per capita.</p> <ol> <li>It is a median figure rather than the mean, which eliminates the positive skew of the extremely high earners.</li> <li>Household income has households as a denominator rather than population, and the number of households has increased as a percentage of the population.</li> </ol> <p>A household now averages about 2 people, down steadily from 2.5 in 1950.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806132724082_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1219\" data-height=\"600\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806132724082.png\" alt=\"A graph showing the growth of a number of individuals Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>So, by using the median, we have largely accounted for income disparity, and by adjusting for a lower number of people per household, we have accounted for the increased expenses that come with it. Both of these adjustments make median real household income less steep of an increase than GDP per capita.</p> <p>However, even after these adjustments, real household income is hovering near all-time highs and is much higher than a decade ago.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806133829741_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1683\" data-height=\"598\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806133829741.png\" alt=\"A graph with a line going up Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>So, if the average consumer has more income in inflation-adjusted dollars, they should be strong, right?</p> <p>Well, there is some conflicting data indicating a weak American consumer.</p> <h2><strong>Weak Consumer</strong></h2> <p>Consumer sentiment is well below normal levels, according to the University of Michigan read.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806134563708_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1684\" data-height=\"607\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806134563708.png\" alt=\"A graph showing the growth of the stock market Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>For the past few years, consumer sentiment has been at levels that are typically only seen during recessions.</p> <p>This is a survey, so there is some subjectivity to it. Perhaps consumers are actually doing well but for some psychological, social or other reasons, they feel like they are struggling.</p> <p>That could be the case, but there is also data indicating real financial difficulties. In November 2024, Apartment List reported cost-burdened households reaching a new record:</p> <blockquote><p>52% of the nation's renters are cost-burdened, meaning they spend more than the recommended 30% of their income on housing. This cost burden rate has been trending up steadily since 2019, as growth in rents has outpaced growth in incomes. In total, today there are over 22 million rent-burden households across the United States, a new record\"</p></blockquote> <p>Historically, cost burdened households have been very region-specific. Certain cities were undersupplied with housing and people were getting priced out. Today, however, it is much more widespread.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806136011121_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"802\" data-height=\"505\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806136011121.png\" alt=\"A map of the united states Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">ApartmentList</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>The sunbelt used to be a beacon of affordability, but now it has joined the coasts in being burdensomely expensive, at least from a housing standpoint.</p> <h2><strong>Reasons for the data discrepancy</strong></h2> <p>It seems contradictory that household income has been growing nicely even after inflation adjustment, and yet people feel poor and perhaps are poor when it comes to affording essentials like housing and food.</p> <p>The most common argument for this contradiction is wealth inequality.</p> <p>While there is some truth in the idea that income disparity has widened, it mathematically cannot be the whole story. The biggest source of growing income disparity is the tail on the wealthy side of the bell curve. While a small percentage of the population is making extreme amounts of money, that has little bearing on the median.</p> <p>The median household has significantly grown their net of inflation income, and yet 51.8% of households are rent burdened (meaning more than 30% of income spent on rent).</p> <p>51.8% includes the median. Therefore, even the households that have grown real income considerably are still somehow feeling this burden.</p> <p>What gives?</p> <p>Well, there have been significant changes to the composition of household income. Specifically, the portion of income that comes from wages and salary has declined considerably, shown in green below.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-1733780613505842_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1224\" data-height=\"498\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-1733780613505842.png\" alt=\"A graph showing a number of employees Description automatically generated with medium confidence\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>These 5 categories add up to 100%, so where is the rest of income coming from?</p> <p>2 categories have increased materially:</p> <ol> <li>Supplements to wages</li> <li>Government checks</li> </ol> <p>Supplements are ways in which employers pay their employees who aren't directly through wages. It could be benefits such as insurance or things like employer contributions to 401ks. The combined supplements have risen sharply.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806142000191_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1686\" data-height=\"589\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806142000191.png\" alt=\"A graph with a line going up Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>These supplements provide very real benefits to employees, but you can't use them to pay for rent or groceries.</p> <p>Thus, even though they are part of income, they feel more like reducing certain costs, such as the cost of independently buying health insurance.</p> <p>Government stimulus and other benefits shot up during COVID and have remained at an above trend level since.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806141955929_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1675\" data-height=\"595\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/9/1843741-17337806141955929.png\" alt=\"A graph with a line going up Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\">FRED</p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>This source of income, unlike employer supplementary benefits, can be and has been used to pay for rent and groceries.</p> <p>I suspect this is a large source of the terribly low consumer sentiment.</p> <p>Future government benefits/stimulus are unknown. So people have been able to pay rent and have been able to buy their groceries, but to the extent these were funded by the stimulus, it creates a certain uneasiness about affordability going forward.</p> <p>Wage/salary funded expenses feel quite a bit better. When someone can afford daily living expenses through their salary and wages, it feels sustainable and in their control. They can forecast a budget and feel confident that they can make ends meet.</p> <p>As such, I posit that the low consumer sentiment is a result of:</p> <ol> <li>Wages/salaries being a smaller portion of income</li> <li>Stimulus being a higher portion of income</li> </ol> <p>I have no opinion on whether stimulus and other such government activity is good or bad. Perhaps it was necessary during the pandemic, that is not for me to decide, and it is outside the scope of this article.</p> <p>The investment relevant point here is that consumer sentiment has long been viewed as a forward indicator of consumer spending. Each time a new low read comes out on consumer sentiment, retail and other directly consumer related stocks tend to sell off.</p> <p>This might not be correct. Consumer spending has been strong in recent years, simultaneous with consumer sentiment being extremely low.</p> <p>Retail and other consumer-facing companies don't really care if the consumer feels good about their ability to spend, they merely care that the consumer actually does spend.</p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p>With all that said, my read on the strength of the American consumer is that forward consumer spending is likely to remain relatively high, even if there is a growing and perhaps rational sense of financial insecurity.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/96502248/image_96502248.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743201-million-dollar-question-american-economy", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 11:33:50"}]}